      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Modern historians view the UN's effectiveness in preventing major 21st-century conflicts as a qualified failure, largely due to the paralysis caused by the veto power of the permanent Security Council members. While the UN excels at humanitarian aid and peacekeeping in localized crises, its structural inability to enforce peace against the will of great powers means it often watches major conflicts erupt. Therefore, its role is more accurately described as managing the fallout of conflict rather than preventing its genesis.",
